name: Cosmic Vase #3
description: Cosmic Vase #3. On the third day, our team that is studying the rivers of Mars, specifically the Hellas Impact Basin, found this object produced by some form of intelligent life. Could this be proof that life has existed on Mars?  This artwork is part of the Cosmic Vases series that depicts the ceramic works of the first terrestrial inhabitants. These archaeological discoveries tend to value, as they are extremely rare and difficult to find. 2000x2000 pixels. Guilherme Ache, 2021.
